The paper discusses a framework for representing context-sensitive knowledge, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of a network formalism suggests a potential connection to knowledge representation and reasoning (cs.KR). The paper also mentions the integration of categorical and uncertain knowledge, which could relate to natural language processing (cs.CL) and probabilistic reasoning (cs.SI).
